'''Peter Sattmann''' (born 26 December 1947 in [[Zwickau]]) is a [[Germany|German]] actor and musician.

== Biography ==
In 1957, Sattmann moved with his parents, Gerda und Ferdinand Sattmann, from Zwickau to [[Friedrichshafen]], where he played in a band when he was twelve years old. He attended the Graf-Zeppelin-Gymnasium up to the eleventh class, when he left to concentrate on acting, moving to [[Munich]] and performing as a street musician.

He married when he was 21 years old, and in 1970 his youngest daughter, Katrin Sattmann, was born. He attended the Neue Münchner Schauspielschule, and in 1969 went to the Deutsches Theater in [[Göttingen]]. He was voted Schauspieler des Jahres in 1975 and in 1977 at the [[Staatstheater Stuttgart|Württembergisches Staatstheater]] in [[Stuttgart]].

Sattmann wrote a number of plays for which he directed the first performances, including "Open End", "Der Erzbischof ist da", "Brave New Man" and "Der Fallschirmspringer", and continued until 1990 at the [[Schiller Theater]].<ref name=prisma>{{cite web | title =Peter Sattmann | work =Prisma Starguide | publisher =Prisma Verlag | url =http://www.prisma.de/person.html?pid=peter_sattmann | accessdate =30 April 2014 | language =German }}</ref><ref name=jedermann>{{cite web | title =Peter Sattmann - Teufel | publisher =Berliner Jedermann Festspiele | year =2014 | url =http://www.jedermann-festspiele.de/?page_id=290 | accessdate =30 April 2014 | language =German }}</ref>

In addition to appearing in films, Sattmann also composed the music for the film "Willkommen im Paradies".<ref name=prisma/> He also composed music for “Kerbels Flucht”, “Der Prinz muss her” and “Das Familienfest”.<ref name=jedermann/><ref>{{cite web | title =Peter Sattmann | publisher =Deutsches Filmhaus | date =27 November 2012 | url =http://www.deutsches-filmhaus.de/bio_er/r-t_spieler/sattmann_peter_bio.htm | accessdate =30 April 2014 | language =German }}</ref>

From 1990 to 1998, he lived with [[Katja Riemann]], and their daughter, [[Paula Riemann]] was born in 1993.<ref name=prisma/>

